<task id="AUTHV2-011" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement BrowserMsalStrategy — full implementation replacing 6-strategy cascade for Dataverse contexts</title>
    <phase>A — Core library rebuild</phase>
    <tags>auth, library, typescript, msal, FULL</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>A-Parallel-1 (with 012)</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Replace the 6-strategy cascade with a clean BrowserMsalStrategy that uses MSAL.js directly. MSAL's localStorage cache handles cross-tab/iframe sharing (no separate BridgeStrategy needed). The acquire() method tries acquireTokenSilent → ssoSilent → acquireTokenPopup in that order. Decode JWT exp on every return to validate freshness.

    Critical: INV-1..INV-7 must be preserved. Read the comparison after implementation and verify no MSAL config value changed from the original SpaarkeAuthProvider constructor.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior MSAL.js engineer.</role>
  <goal>
    BrowserMsalStrategy.acquire() returns a TokenResult with valid (non-expired) accessToken. Uses MSAL's localStorage + cookie-state. No popup in steady state (verified by MSAL regression test from spaarke-sso-binding.md).
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §4.4 (INV-1..INV-7)</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md §"Required MSAL Configuration"</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/MsalSilentStrategy.ts (existing — fold logic into BrowserMsalStrategy)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/MsalPopupStrategy.ts (existing — fold logic)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/config.ts (resolveTenantFromXrm + resolveDefaultAuthority — INV-3 source)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read MsalSilentStrategy.ts and MsalPopupStrategy.ts — understand the existing acquireTokenSilent + ssoSilent + acquireTokenPopup flow.</step>
    <step>Implement BrowserMsalStrategy.acquire(): try MSAL acquireTokenSilent first (with cached account from MSAL); fallback to ssoSilent with loginHint from Xrm; final fallback to acquireTokenPopup. Decode JWT exp from result.accessToken and validate it's not within 5-min expiry buffer.</step>
    <step>Implement BrowserMsalStrategy.clearCache(): call MSAL's removeAccount on the active account (which clears MSAL's localStorage cache for that account).</step>
    <step>Preserve loginHint resolution from Xrm.userSettings.userName via frame-walk (MsalSilentStrategy lines 12-30).</step>
    <step>Delete MsalSilentStrategy.ts + MsalPopupStrategy.ts; logic is now inside BrowserMsalStrategy.</step>
    <step>Update SpaarkeAuthProvider to call strategy.acquire() instead of the old 6-strategy cascade. Keep in-memory CacheStrategy as a wrapper (full simplification in 012).</step>
    <step>Run tsc --noEmit. Run the MSAL regression test from spaarke-sso-binding.md (clear all caches → close browser → reopen → verify no popup).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>BrowserMsalStrategy.acquire() returns non-expired tokens.</criterion>
    <criterion>JWT exp validation with 5-min buffer is present in code.</criterion>
    <criterion>loginHint via Xrm frame-walk preserved.</criterion>
    <criterion>MsalSilentStrategy.ts + MsalPopupStrategy.ts deleted.</criterion>
    <criterion>MSAL regression test passes: authority in console log contains tenant GUID, no popup.</criterion>
    <criterion>INV-1, INV-2, INV-3 visible in code with comments referencing the audit doc invariants.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
